FT  20 MAR 92 / UK Company News: Modest advance to Pounds 2.64m at Ferrum
Ferrum Holdings, the engineering group, reported a 3 per cent advance in
pre-tax profits, from Pounds 2.57m to Pounds 2.64m, in the 1991 year.
Turnover was higher at Pounds 44.3m, against Pounds 41.9m.
The pre-tax figure was struck after lower net interest charges of Pounds
324,000 (Pounds 705,000) and an exceptional provision of Pounds 250,000
relating to the company's planned move to Edinburgh.
Earnings per share came out at 7.13p (8.16p) and a final dividend of 1.4p is
proposed making a total of 2.5p (2.25p).
